currentTime

public double currentTime()
Returns the elapsed time since the simulation started. This is a global clock that should not be used within nodes for coordination purposes. The values returned by this method are best used to compute performance statistics, such as the average number of messages sent by unit of time...

Returns the elapsed time since the simulation started in real time.

setSimulationMaxTimeWarp

public void setSimulationMaxTimeWarp(double factor)
Controls the speed of the simulation relative to real time. For instance, passing 2.0 will cause the simulation to run up to twice as fast as real time.
